@marian-pritsak I am trying to figure out why port channel is delayed.
I see that PortChannel0001 is created in linux but "ok" mark in STATE DB is delayed by ~1 min.
@pavel-shirshov could you please help to figure out why?

@keboliu in some ASIC vendor ingress mirroring can be on egress ACL. this is why @stcheng asked not to limit the solution for it.
Now the question is how we can know which vendor supports this option or not. Please check for each what action are supported and allow it. Please verify the get API for each egress/ingress if it supported the relevant action from SAI_ACL_TABLE_ATTR_ACL_ACTION_TYPE_LIST.
for example: SAI_ACL_ACTION_TYPE_MIRROR_EGRESS and SAI_ACL_ACTION_TYPE_MIRROR_INGRESS

@nikos-github 
since the initial configuration always comes from port_config.ini, ports will always have alias (ini file parser uses port name if alias not specified)
the only scenario which will be different after this change is when you intentionally remove aliases from the config_db.json. In that case after s2s upgrade ports config will remain without aliases (previously aliases were always recreated from ini file).

@nikos-github 
code always uses the DB.
port_config.ini is used only once on start and only when there is no ports info in the DB
